custom-block.comment: SideEffect: Displays a map on the stage of your current location in real life.
Side Effect: Zooms in within the stages map based on the set zoom value.
Side Effect: Updates the board after including the new changes.
Output: Returns current longitude of your sprites location as an integer.
Output: Returns current latitude of your sprites location as an integer.
Output: Contains a list of your current latitude and longitude as coordinates.

Input: An integer for the x input, and an integer for the y input. SIde Effect: Moves the stages map view by an x and y. Modifies the sprites location to be the center of the map. Can be continuously pressed to change location by (x, y) for N times.
Input: Longitude and Latitude coordinates as integers. Side Effect: Changes the map's location to the new Longitude and Latitude, instead of your default location.
Intput: Current Stage Map. Output: Returns current stage map as a costume.
Input: Map type slection. Side Effect: Changes the type of map used to move sprite. Essentially changes the background among the availible options.
Input: Integer Value Side Effect: Modifies how far zoomed in your map should be from your current location.

scripts.comment: Example: - Grabs your current location - Set zoom to a size of 50 - Changes the sprite location to be centered at the UC Berkeley Sather Tower
